One approach you could take is to create a separate popup component that you can render wherever you need it in your application. Here's an example of what that might look like:
```javascript
import React from 'react';

const Popup = ({ message, onClose }) => {
  return (
    <div className="popup">
      <p>{message}</p>
      <button onClick={onClose}>Close</button>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Popup;
```
This component takes two props: `message` (the content of the popup) and `onClose` (a function that will be called when the user clicks the "Close" button). You can style the popup however you like using CSS.

To use this component globally, you'll need to render it at a high level in your component tree so that it can be accessed from any other component. One way to do this is to use a React context:
```javascript
import React, { createContext, useState } from 'react';
import Popup from './Popup';

const PopupContext = createContext({
  showPopup: () => {},
});

const PopupProvider = ({ children }) => {
  const [popupMessage, setPopupMessage] = useState('');
  const [showPopup, setShowPopup] = useState(false);

  const handleClosePopup = () => {
    setShowPopup(false);
  };

  const displayPopup = (message) => {
    setPopupMessage(message);
    setShowPopup(true);
  };

  return (
    <PopupContext.Provider value={{ showPopup: displayPopup }}>
      {children}
      {showPopup && (
        <Popup message={popupMessage} onClose={handleClosePopup} />
      )}
    </PopupContext.Provider>
  );
};

export { PopupContext, PopupProvider };
```
Here, we've defined a `PopupContext` that provides a `showPopup` function that can be used to display the popup from any component that is a child of the `PopupProvider`. The `PopupProvider` component renders the `Popup` component if `showPopup` is true.

To use the popup from a child component, you can use the `useContext` hook to access the `showPopup` function:
```javascript
import React, { useContext } from 'react';
import { PopupContext } from './PopupProvider';

